wires, and a few other things here and there -- and the market is enormous.=
 That means lots of companies offering similarish products and either compe=
ting for the same customers directly or going after ever-more-targeted nich=
es. Starting from scratch today, it=E2=80=99s nearly impossible to profitab=
ly build a neobank. There are too many competitors converging on the same p=
roduct suite targeting the same customers. The CACs are too damn high.=C2=
